Apple recently introduced its fourth-generation  iPod , revised with a new interface similar to that found on the  iPod mini  and a new feature called Shuffle Songs.   The new iPod features Appleâ€™s Click Wheel with five push buttons for one-handed navigation, up to 12 hours of battery life, and Shuffle Songs, a new command in the main menu, which gives users instant access to their music library.  The iPod is available in 20GB ($299) and 40GB ($399) capacities.